{
  "texts": [
    "It has been found to significantly improve students' mathematical achievement and problem-solving skills compared to traditional teaching methods (Septian et al., 2020; Bedada & Machaba, 2022).",
    "The software's ability to combine geometry, algebra, and calculus makes it a versatile tool for independently exploring mathematical concepts (Majerek, 2014).",
    "The present study offers valuable insights into the research landscape of GeoGebra in mathematics education through the application of bibliometric analysis.",
    "However, the authors acknowledge several limitations that present opportunities for future investigations in this domain.",
    "Notably, the data scope of the current analysis is confined to the SCOPUS database, which may have overlooked significant contributions published in other databases, such as WSCC and ERIC, that are not indexed within this source."
  ]
}